Adding a Gaussian noise to the power flow results

In [52]:
meas_P_mask = ps.measurements['type'].str.startswith('P')
meas_Q_mask = ps.measurements['type'].str.startswith('Q')
meas_PQ_mask = meas_P_mask | meas_Q_mask
num_PQ_meas = np.count_nonzero(meas_PQ_mask)
PQ_var = 0.01  #Gaussian noise variance for active/reactive power measurements
noise_PQ = np.random.randn(num_PQ_meas)*PQ_var
ps.measurements.loc[meas_PQ_mask,'value'] += noise_PQ
In [53]:
meas_V_mask = ps.measurements['type'].str.startswith('V')
num_V_meas = np.count_nonzero(meas_V_mask)
V_var = 0.005 #Gaussian noise variance for voltage magnitude measurements
noise_V = np.random.randn(num_V_meas)*V_var
ps.measurements.loc[meas_V_mask,'value'] += noise_V
